 and inspire young singers. In this ground-breaking book, Stephen Hastings analyzes more than four hundred of the great tenor's recordings, comparing them with the output of a hundred other tenors, from Caruso to Alagna. The repertoire ranges from brief art songs by Schubert and Sibelius to entire opera recordings--some madein the studio, others captured live. What emerges is a richly layered portrait of this most musical of singers. As Hastings's comparisons demonstrate, Björling left his unique imprint on all the scores he sang, combining a perennial freshness of approach with the richly inflected phrasing made possible by a perfectly honed technique. Born in London and educated in Oxford, Stephen Hastings has been the Milan correspondent of Opera Newssince 1991 and editor in chief of the Italian monthly Musica for the past twelve years.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBjörling, Jussi, -- 1911-1960 -- Performances.;Vocal music -- Performances.;Tenors (Singers) -- Biography. 0aTenors (Singers)vBiography. 0aVocal musicxPerformances. 4aFilm & Theatre. 4aMusic. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Opera.2bisacsh  aJussi Björling.  aSwedish tenor.  acomparative analysis.  amusic history.  aopera.  arecorded legacy.  atechnique.  atenor singing.  avocal artistry.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978158046773540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781580467735423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781580467735/original  a978-3-11-143139-0  Boydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013b2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles